-------------  Here's all "the dirt" on my plantable papers:
STORING YOUR PAPER: Store your paper in any cool (not freezing), dry area that is not subject to extreme variations in temperature and humidity. Some products come packaged in an acid-free plastic envelope. If you will not be using your plantable paper right away, open the packaging so the seeds can breathe. For best germination, you should plant your paper within 12-18 months of purchase.
PLANTING YOUR PAPER: To force your plantable paper indoors, moisten the paper until damp but not wet, put in a plastic jar and cover with plastic wrap. Place in a warm, sunny window and you will see little seedlings in about 2 weeks! If planting outdoors, wait until all danger of frost has passed, then rake the soil, scatter the paper onto the soil, cover with 1/4 inch of topsoil, water and keep moist until germination, approximately 6 to 8 weeks.

Product name: Bozak Speaker B207A B200X replacement Coaxial 12/15 inch Woofer and Tweeter Driver
Description:
This is an artifact of the high end 1960s audiophile world. It is is the combination of the B-199A woofer and two B-200X tweeters. The tweeters are mounted to an aluminum frame that can be removed from the B-199A woofer if needed.
If you grew up in the 1950s through the 1970s you probably would lust after those Bozak unicorns that were advertised in magazines of those days. I'm guessing you must have finally brought a pair home only to find that they were ridden hard and put away wet.
A friend of mine gave me a doghouse sized speaker cabinet as a gift because I helped him move a tank of a nineteenth century piano. Out of an incurable curiosity to find out what is inside of everything, I opened it up as soon as I got home. To my surprise, A BOZAK! I immediately put it back together and hooked it up to one channel of my amplifier, and listened in mono to this glorious monster. It produced big clean, clear sound. There is no voice coil rubbing, and the tweeters seem clear and crisp. If I had two of these you wouldn't be reading this, but I prefer stereo.
 I did some looking around on the Internets and found very few replacement drivers like this one; I checked other's pricing and decided to lowball them. This needs to find a home in an original Bozak cabinet.
This is one Bozak woofer/tweeter unit. The two B-200X tweeters are mounted in front of the woofer. No tears are apparent on any of the cones. There are residual wood fibers from the previous cabinet still pressed on to the front face of the crinkle coated frame, and some typical patina associated with 50 year old hardware, but this thing still sings well.
